New Records: Antetokounmpo had six offensive rebounds to increase his career total to 1,469 and become Milwaukee's career leader.
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 31 points and 16 rebounds.
The Bucks snapped a six-game skid with a 123-100 victory over the Jazz.
Utah led 71-70 before the Bucks took command with a 17-1 run late in the third quarter.
Antetokounmpo picked up his fourth foul with 10:26 left in the third quarter but didn't pick up another foul during that stretch and helped spark the 17-1 run.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks hadn’t lost six straight games since March 2015 and avoided their first seven-game skid since March 2014.
Jordan Clarkson had 18 points off the bench to lead the Jazz.
Milwaukee coach Doc Rivers shuffled his lineup by giving Andre Jackson Jr. his first start of the season and moving Gary Trent Jr. to a bench role.
